==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English [[major]], borrowed from {{L.}} ''[[maior]]'' (''comparative of [[magnus]]''), from Proto-Indo-European ''*maǵ-yes-'' "greater", comparative of ''*maǵ-, *meǵ-'', "great".

